cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper introduces a new type of neural network called Self-Delimiting Neural Networks (SLIM NNs) and proposes a learning algorithm for them. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses algorithmic information theory and probability theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The proposed learning algorithm involves optimizing the program search, which could also place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses using SLIM NNs for robot control tasks, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
